{
  "text": "Remark 3.3. We point out that Proposition 3.2 is essentially an application of Leray-Hopf energy inequality and the well-known fact (cf. [CITATION_1] ) that having control on the growth of the rate of global energy dissipation, \u01eb := sup t\u22650 \u01eb(t), where \u01eb(t) := \u03bd \u2207u(t) 2 L 2 , can sustain exponential decay in the spectrum of the corresponding solution. The need for proving Proposition 3.2 comes from the fact that we require detailed information of the decay rates of the solution and the particular effect on it from the body force, which is not immediately available from [CITATION_2] , where the case of having a non-potential force is not treated.",
